timeline.bodyText:
It's impossible to know what this means, without going to look it up.
My usual suggestion here is to replace a boolean flag with an enum, which is plenty more semantic:
enum PerformMoonLaunch {
    YEA_DO_IT,
    NAH_CHIEF_NO_THANKS;
}

How it looks when being passed as a flag:
// Oh! it's time to go to the moon...
nasa.runHoustonOperations(PerformMoonLaunch.YEA_DO_IT);

vs. the original with a boolean flag:
// Oh okay, we should run the operations, for real? Or... wait, why is there a bool?
nasa.runHoustonOperations(true);

