replies.bodyText:
It isn't much extra complexity, really:
boolean someFlag;

vs.
enum SomeFlag {
    TRUE,
    FALSE
}

3 lines more --- none more, if you cheat:
enum SomeFlag { TRUE, FALSE }

:-)

timeline.bodyText:
Instead of having a constructor which allows a null field, provide an overloaded constructor that doesn't require the field. This way, the class never accepts null. (You might use one internally, but that's your own business.)
e.g.
// Huh? What's null?
nasa.fuelUp(rockets, null, fuelSequences);

vs.
nasa.fuelUp(rockets, fuelSequences);

Or:
nasa.fuelUp(rockets, fuelContainers, fuelSequences);

