timeline.bodyText:
You can probably skip the doAnswer stuff, and then just use eq to check what is passed in.
Most of these tests should just be like:
// Arrange some options foo, bar, baz
Foo foo = new Foo();
Bar bar = mock(Bar.class);
Baz baz = getABaz();

// Act by calling Auth API
auth.signUp(foo, bar, baz, whatever);

// veriify that the mobile client was called in a certain way...
verfiy(mobileClient).signUp(eq(foo), eq(baz));

Or, in some cases you might not be able to useeq, directly. In which case you can do:
auth.signUo("foo", "bar", "baz");

ArgumentCaptor<TypeYouCantMake> whatDidItGiveMe = ArgumentCaptor.forClass(TypeYouCantMake.class);
verify(mobileClient).signUp(whatDidItGiveMe.capture(), eq(bar), eq(baz));

Foo foo = whatDidItGiveMe.value().getSomeContainedField();
assertEquals(expectedFoo, foo); // Ah!!  the thing it gave us _contained_ an expected foo.

